Checklist for the time when a new version is about to be released:

1.  Add some functions from file: addthesefunctions 
2.  Make some changes from ToDo list. 
3.  Check spelling.
4.  Check examples. <-- currently broken.
5.  Check comments match examples: '<!-- RandomComment -->'.
    --> grep RandomComment *.xml ../lib/*.gd
6.  Check version number
7.  Check release date.
8.  Check contents of GAP-DIR/dev/links.txt 
9.  Check citation info.
10. Comment disclaimer in doc/preface.xml
11. Build the manual.
    (run gap in GAP-DIR/pkg/yags/doc/ and then Read("docsettings.gap"); )
12. Clean up backup files; dump Trash.
13. (git add), (git commit) changes.
14. (git push) to repository.
15. Create a release in GitHub.
16. Pull from webpage 
    --> make (volver a lanzar el crontab cuando se arregle el wget).
17. Update webpage data (update Makefile)
    --> make version
18. Update webpage (Â¡Ismael!).
19. Check that all links in GAP-DIR/dev/links.txt work. 
20. Alert on yagsnews@xamanek.izt.uam.mx (and others?)
---------
21. Create a new version (like: 0.0.7-dev) before editing further.
22. Uncomment disclamer in doc/preface.xml again. 
